Answer.Ans1: The Satish Dhawan Space Centre (SDSC) was named after Dr. Satish Dhawan, an eminent Indian scientist and former chairman of the Indian Space Research Organisation (ISRO). The center was renamed in his honor on September 5, 2002, shortly after his passing. Dr. Satish Dhawan played a crucial role in shaping and advancing India's space program, making significant contributions to the country's space research and development. Renaming the space center after him was a way to pay tribute to his immense contributions and honor his legacy in the field of space science and technology.
Answer.Res1: The Satish Dhawan Space Centre (SDSC) was renamed in honor of Dr. Satish Dhawan as a tribute to his significant contributions to the Indian space program. Dr. Dhawan was a renowned scientist and engineer who played a pivotal role in shaping and advancing India's space research and development initiatives.
